				<td colspan="2"><span>I honestly never used it 8/.
<br />

<br />
The main reason you would want to increase your singing power is to sing PoV. Unless you are in a Main tank group or a clr group <i>and</i> there resists isnt maxed without Amp, then maybe you might consider it.
<br />

<br />
Keep in mind that our mods are base capped at 3.6 (go up to 4.2 with AT and ET)
<br />

<br />
So lets say you have a VoTS (0.6) and SM4 (0.8) this made it to 1.4 all togheter. So you need a 2.8 sing mod to reach 4.2
<br />

<br />
On another point of view, a 0.6 mod add ~48 more resists to PoV, if you really need it, use it.. otherwise, don't bother.
<br />

<br />
PS. VoTS &gt; Amp, so if you don't have at least a VoTS go get it or die!</span></td>
